name: ISYANA: THE 4TH ALBUM SHOWCASE LIVE ON TOUR
description: The long-awaited fourth studio album, self-titled ISYANA is an extension of the latest EP, a turning and burning point of her life. Despite the perplexing journey, she remains true, vulnerable, and honest in her stories. Isyana Sarasvati converse through classical rock, electronic tunes, and distortions of melodies. A roller coaster of emotion through an evolution of virtuous sounds.This intimate showcase of ISYANA, which integrates a mind-blowing stage act with stunning visuals and lighting, is an opportunity that cannot be missed. All of this will be brought closer to you in July and August.

name: Rhytm Of Love
description:
Join us for an extraordinary evening filled with love and joy at the "Rhythm of Love" concert. This enchanting event will take place at Bengkel SCBD, starting at 9pm. Prepare to be serenaded by the sensational voices of Yura Yunita and the celebrated duo, Yovie and Nuno.

Immerse yourself in a night of captivating melodies, soulful performances, and heartfelt lyrics that will touch your heart. The concert promises to create an unforgettable atmosphere, where love and music intertwine to create pure bliss.

As the clock strikes 9pm, the stage will come alive with the enchanting performances of these renowned artists. Yura Yunita, known for her soulful voice and heartfelt ballads, will captivate you with her emotive renditions. Yovie and Nuno, a duo synonymous with romantic hits, will serenade you with their timeless classics.

Bengkel SCBD, renowned for its state-of-the-art facilities and exceptional acoustics, will provide the perfect setting for this magical evening. Its intimate ambiance and carefully curated atmosphere will enhance your concert experience, allowing you to fully immerse yourself in the music.

Come and be part of this extraordinary celebration of love and joy. Grab your tickets now and get ready to indulge in an unforgettable night of soul-stirring performances at the "Rhythm of Love" concert with Yura Yunita and Yovie and Nuno.
